75, \"to\": 1082}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But having become a mother for the first time in 2022, she returned from maternity leave to find a generation of upstarts on the tear and had to scrap hard to win her place back.\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mother\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"maternity leave\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"a generation\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"upstarts\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"the tear\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"her place\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, when Britain claimed silver behind the Germans at the World Championships 12 months ago she was not in the three.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9971626756041139, \"rank\": 0.0028453976733520334, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"the Germans\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Capewell was but at 25 these are her first Games - though not a first Games for the Capewells, late father Nigel having ridden in the Paralympics at Atlanta 1996 and Sydney 2000.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Capewell\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"her first Games\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"the Capewells\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"late father Nigel\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"Atlanta\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"Sydney\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1558}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And then there is Finucane, the youngest at 21 and already poised to inherit the golden girl crown passed from Pendleton to Dame Laura Kenny as she targets the same hat-trick of Olympic sprint golds once achieved by Sir Chris Hoy and Sir Jason Kenny.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pendleton,_Oregon\", \"score\": 0.664823570386926, \"rank\": 0.2783934316033139, \"text\": \"Pendleton\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pendleton,_Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pendleton,_Oregon\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\"}, {\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Finucane\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the golden girl crown\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"the same hat-trick\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sprint golds\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pull it off and she will surely become the breakout sensation of the Games.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1892, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the breakout sensation\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1891}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shorn of those names made household byOlympicspast, Britain's track cyclists have flown a little beneath the broader radar in the run up to Paris.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9971626756041139, \"rank\": 0.0028453976733520334, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2034, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.105276213932344e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those names\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"household byOlympicspast\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"the broader radar\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"the run\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The talk from those in the know, though, has been bullish.\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The talk\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2049}, {\"ngram\": \"the know\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hoy called Finucane a \\\"superstar\\\" in-waiting.\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hoy\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"Finucane\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2119}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"superstar\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2132}, {\"ngram\": \"waiting\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenny said this was the best women's sprint team she had ever seen.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kenny\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"the best women's sprint team\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jason has been a little quieter, understandably, since he is here in an official capacity, as a sprint coach.\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.9875400453265206, \"rank\": 0.012560432263739084, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a little quieter\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2245}, {\"ngram\": \"an official capacity\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint coach\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But whether they know the faces or not, when the British public tune into the velodrome, they expect gold.\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the faces\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB again finished top of cycling's medal table in Tokyo, for the fourth Olympics in a row, but needed more help than usual from beyond the velodrome.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2432, \"end\": 2439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999554348, \"rank\": 2.6593823178487115e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2487, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0